#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.63"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.63:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.63:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.63:0.3"
msgid "63. Puttamaṃsasutta"
msgstr "63. A Child’s Flesh"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.98"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.63:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ …"
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.63:1.2"
msgid ""
"“cattārome, bhikkhave, āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā sambhavesīnaṃ vā "
"anuggahāya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these four fuels. They maintain sentient beings that "
"have been born and help those that are about to be born."

msgctxt "sn12.63:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn12.63:1.4"
msgid ""
"Kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, "
"viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention "
"the third, and consciousness the fourth."

msgctxt "sn12.63:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā sambhavesīnaṃ "
"vā anuggahāya."
msgstr ""
"These are the four fuels that maintain sentient beings that have been born "
"and help those that are about to be born."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.63:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, kabaḷīkāro āhāro daṭṭhabbo?"
msgstr "And how should you regard solid food?"

#. VAR: jāyampatikā → jayampatikā (bj, pts1-2) | jāyapatikā (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn12.63:2.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dve jāyampatikā parittaṃ sambalaṃ ādāya kantāramaggaṃ "
"paṭipajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a couple who were husband and wife set out to cross a desert, taking "
"limited supplies."

msgctxt "sn12.63:2.3"
msgid "Tesamassa ekaputtako piyo manāpo."
msgstr "They had an only child, dear and beloved."

msgctxt "sn12.63:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tesaṃ, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ jāyampatikānaṃ kantāragatānaṃ yā parittā "
"sambalamattā, sā parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"As the couple were crossing the desert their limited quantity of supplies "
"would run out,"

#. VAR: anatiṇṇo → anittiṇṇo (bj) | anithiṇṇo (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.63:2.5"
msgid "Siyā ca nesaṃ kantārāvaseso anatiṇṇo."
msgstr "and they’d still have the rest of the desert to cross."

msgctxt "sn12.63:2.6"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ jāyampatikānaṃ evamassa:"
msgstr "Then it would occur to that couple:"

#. VAR: pariyādiṇṇā → pariyādinnā (bj, s1-3, km) | pariyādānaṃ (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.63:2.7"
msgid "‘amhākaṃ kho yā parittā sambalamattā sā parikkhīṇā pariyādiṇṇā."
msgstr "‘Our limited quantity of supplies has run out,"

#. VAR: anittiṇṇo → anitthiṇṇo (s1-3, km) | anithiṇṇo (pts1-2) | anatiṇṇo (mr)
msgctxt "sn12.63:2.8"
msgid "Atthi cāyaṃ kantārāvaseso anittiṇṇo."
msgstr "and we still have the rest of the desert to cross."

msgctxt "sn12.63:2.9"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ imaṃ ekaputtakaṃ piyaṃ manāpaṃ vadhitvā vallūrañca soṇḍikañca "
"karitvā puttamaṃsāni khādantā evaṃ taṃ kantārāvasesaṃ nitthareyyāma, mā "
"sabbeva tayo vinassimhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t we kill our only child, so dear and beloved, and prepare dried and "
"spiced meat? Then we can make it across the desert by eating our child’s "
"flesh. Let not all three perish.’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:2.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te, bhikkhave, dve jāyampatikā taṃ ekaputtakaṃ piyaṃ manāpaṃ "
"vadhitvā vallūrañca soṇḍikañca karitvā puttamaṃsāni khādantā evaṃ taṃ "
"kantārāvasesaṃ nitthareyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then that couple would kill their only child, so dear and beloved, and "
"prepare dried and spiced meat. They’d make it across the desert by eating "
"their child’s flesh."

msgctxt "sn12.63:2.11"
msgid "Te puttamaṃsāni ceva khādeyyuṃ, ure ca paṭipiseyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"And as they’d eat their child’s flesh, they’d beat their breasts and cry:"

# This is very interesting psychologically. Normally you’d think they’d say “what have we done?” But their not consumed with guilt, they feel for their child.
msgctxt "sn12.63:2.12"
msgid "‘kahaṃ, ekaputtaka, kahaṃ, ekaputtakā’ti."
msgstr "‘Where are you, our only child? Where are you, our only child?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.99"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.63:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.2"
msgid ""
"api nu te davāya vā āhāraṃ āhāreyyuṃ, madāya vā āhāraṃ āhāreyyuṃ, maṇḍanāya "
"vā āhāraṃ āhāreyyuṃ, vibhūsanāya vā āhāraṃ āhāreyyun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would they eat that food for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration?”"

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.4"
msgid ""
"“Nanu te, bhikkhave, yāvadeva kantārassa nittharaṇatthāya āhāraṃ "
"āhāreyyun”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Wouldn’t they eat that food just so they could make it across the desert?”"

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.6"
msgid "“‘Evameva khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, kabaḷīkāro āhāro daṭṭhabbo’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "“I say that this is how you should regard solid food."

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.7"
msgid ""
"Kabaḷīkāre, bhikkhave, āhāre pariññāte pañca kāmaguṇiko rāgo pariññāto hoti."
msgstr ""
"When solid food is completely understood, desire for the five kinds of "
"sensual stimulation is completely understood."

msgctxt "sn12.63:3.8"
msgid ""
"Pañca kāmaguṇike rāge pariññāte natthi taṃ saṃyojanaṃ yena saṃyojanena "
"saṃyutto ariyasāvako puna imaṃ lokaṃ āgaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"When desire for the five kinds of sensual stimulation is completely "
"understood, a noble disciple is bound by no fetter that might return them "
"again to this world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.63:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, phassāhāro daṭṭhabbo?"
msgstr "And how should you regard contact as fuel?"

# Note that this context shows that nissaya in such cases cannot mean “leaning”.
#. VAR: kuṭṭañce → kuḍḍañce (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.63:4.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gāvī niccammā kuṭṭañce nissāya tiṭṭheyya. Ye "
"kuṭṭanissitā pāṇā te naṃ khādeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a flayed cow. If she stands by a wall, the creatures on "
"the wall bite her."

msgctxt "sn12.63:4.3"
msgid "Rukkhañce nissāya tiṭṭheyya, ye rukkhanissitā pāṇā te naṃ khādeyyuṃ."
msgstr "If she stands under a tree, the creatures in the tree bite her."

msgctxt "sn12.63:4.4"
msgid "Udakañce nissāya tiṭṭheyya, ye udakanissitā pāṇā te naṃ khādeyyuṃ."
msgstr "If she stands in some water, the creatures in the water bite her."

msgctxt "sn12.63:4.5"
msgid "Ākāsañce nissāya tiṭṭheyya, ye ākāsanissitā pāṇā te naṃ khādeyyuṃ."
msgstr "If she stands in the open, the creatures in the open bite her."

#. VAR: nissāya tiṭṭheyya, ye tannissitā → nissāya tiṭṭheyya ye tannissitā tannissitā (sī1, pā1-2), nissāya tiṭṭheyya ye taṃ nissitā taṃ nissitā (syā1-3, kaṃ)
msgctxt "sn12.63:4.6"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ yadeva hi sā, bhikkhave, gāvī niccammā nissāya tiṭṭheyya, ye tannissitā "
"pāṇā te naṃ khādeyyuṃ."
msgstr "Wherever that flayed cow stands, the creatures there would bite her."

msgctxt "sn12.63:4.7"
msgid "Evameva khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘phassāhāro daṭṭhabbo’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "I say that this is how you should regard contact as fuel."

msgctxt "sn12.63:4.8"
msgid "Phasse, bhikkhave, āhāre pariññāte tisso vedanā pariññātā honti."
msgstr ""
"When contact as fuel is completely understood, the three feelings are "
"completely understood."

#. VAR: uttarikaraṇīyanti → uttariṃ karaṇīyanti (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.63:4.9"
msgid ""
"Tīsu vedanāsu pariññātāsu ariyasāvakassa natthi kiñci uttarikaraṇīyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"When the three feelings are completely understood, a noble disciple has "
"nothing further to do, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.100"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.63:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, manosañcetanāhāro daṭṭhabbo?"
msgstr "And how should you regard mental intention as fuel?"

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā puṇṇā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ "
"vītadhūmānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, filled "
"with glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked."

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.3"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo."
msgstr ""
"Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, "
"who wants to be happy and recoils from pain."

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.4"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ dve balavanto purisā nānābāhāsu gahetvā taṃ aṅgārakāsuṃ "
"upakaḍḍheyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then two strong men would grab them by the arms and drag them towards the "
"pit of glowing coals."

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa ārakāvassa cetanā ārakā patthanā ārakā "
"paṇidhi."
msgstr "Then that person’s intention, aim, and wish would be to get far away."

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.7"
msgid "Evañhi, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa hoti:"
msgstr "Because that person would think:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.8"
msgid ""
"‘imañcāhaṃ aṅgārakāsuṃ papatissāmi, tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchāmi "
"maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If I fall in that pit of glowing coals, that will result in my death or "
"deadly pain.’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.9"
msgid "Evameva khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘manosañcetanāhāro daṭṭhabbo’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "I say that this is how you should regard mental intention as fuel."

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.10"
msgid ""
"Manosañcetanāya, bhikkhave, āhāre pariññāte tisso taṇhā pariññātā honti."
msgstr ""
"When mental intention as fuel is completely understood, the three cravings "
"are completely understood."

msgctxt "sn12.63:5.11"
msgid ""
"Tīsu taṇhāsu pariññātāsu ariyasāvakassa natthi kiñci uttarikaraṇīyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"When the three cravings are completely understood, a noble disciple has "
"nothing further to do, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.63:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, viññāṇāhāro daṭṭhabbo?"
msgstr "And how should you regard consciousness as fuel?"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā rañño dasseyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a criminal and present him to the "
"king, saying:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, deva, coro āgucārī, imassa yaṃ icchasi taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this is a bandit, a criminal. Punish him as you will.’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ rājā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "The king would say:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.5"
msgid "‘gacchatha, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ pubbaṇhasamayaṃ sattisatena hanathā’ti."
msgstr "‘Go, my men, and strike this man in the morning with a hundred spears!’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ pubbaṇhasamayaṃ sattisatena haneyyuṃ."
msgstr "The king’s men did as they were told."

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.7"
msgid "Atha rājā majjhanhikasamayaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Then at midday the king would say:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.8"
msgid "‘ambho, kathaṃ so puriso’ti?"
msgstr "‘My men, how is that man?’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.9"
msgid "‘Tatheva, deva, jīvatī’ti."
msgstr "‘He’s still alive, Your Majesty.’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ rājā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "The king would say:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.11"
msgid "‘gacchatha, bho, taṃ purisaṃ majjhanhikasamayaṃ sattisatena hanathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Go, my men, and strike this man in the middle of the day with a hundred "
"spears!’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.12"
msgid "Tamenaṃ majjhanhikasamayaṃ sattisatena haneyyuṃ."
msgstr "The king’s men did as they were told."

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.13"
msgid "Atha rājā sāyanhasamayaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Then late in the afternoon the king would say:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.14"
msgid "‘ambho, kathaṃ so puriso’ti?"
msgstr "‘My men, how is that man?’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.15"
msgid "‘Tatheva, deva, jīvatī’ti."
msgstr "‘He’s still alive, Your Majesty.’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.16"
msgid "Tamenaṃ rājā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "The king would say:"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.17"
msgid "‘gacchatha, bho, taṃ purisaṃ sāyanhasamayaṃ sattisatena hanathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Go, my men, and strike this man in the late afternoon with a hundred "
"spears!’"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.18"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sāyanhasamayaṃ sattisatena haneyyuṃ."
msgstr "The king’s men did as they were told."

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.19"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.20"
msgid ""
"api nu so puriso divasaṃ tīhi sattisatehi haññamāno tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ "
"domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvediyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would that man experience pain and distress from being struck with three "
"hundred spears a day?”"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.21"
msgid ""
"“Ekissāpi, bhante, sattiyā haññamāno tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvediyetha;"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, that man would experience pain and distress from being struck with one "
"spear,"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.22"
msgid "ko pana vādo tīhi sattisatehi haññamāno”ti."
msgstr "how much more so three hundred spears!”"

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.23"
msgid "“Evameva khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, viññāṇāhāro daṭṭhabboti vadāmi."
msgstr "“I say that this is how you should regard consciousness as fuel."

msgctxt "sn12.63:6.24"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇe, bhikkhave, āhāre pariññāte nāmarūpaṃ pariññātaṃ hoti, nāmarūpe "
"pariññāte ariyasāvakassa natthi kiñci uttarikaraṇīyanti vadāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When consciousness as fuel is completely understood, name and form is "
"completely understood. When name and form are completely understood, a noble "
"disciple has nothing further to do, I say.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.63:6.25"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
